oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SOME PROBLEMS CAUSED BY BUILDING THE CROSS DYKE ACROSS TOKYO BAY
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Ito, Takeshi
Hino, Mikio
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: cross dike
dike
Tokyo Bay
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Two hydraulic problems anticipated from the construction of a dike across Tokyo Bay, i e water circulation and 'harbor paradox' are discussed from results of numerical experiments Especially, a new technique has been devised for the investigation of response characteristics of the bay to obtain all the information by only one run.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 10 (1966): Proceedings of 10th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Tokyo, Japan, 1966.; 84
